{
 "name": "RPlog_Fay_and_Morganna",
 "title": "Sheltering from the Rain at Hideaway Beach",
 "summary": "When a sudden downpour drives them to shelter inside an abandoned lighthouse on Caspar's Hideaway Beach, the Ambassador Fay and the scarred, one-eyed mercenary Morganna fall into a long, candid conversation beside a fire Morganna kindles by blasting a pile of musty wood. Their talk circles warily around the 'red-eyed bastard' Ozzle, the Force-user who once tried to control Morganna's mind and now keeps tabs on her, leaving her to hide out in the rain rather than return to KOS. Morganna confesses a brutal philosophy of kill-or-be-killed, demonstrating it by snatching and snapping the neck of a rodent and tossing it into the flames, even as glimpses of a more intelligent, less cold-blooded nature flicker across her ruined face. Fay listens with patient, disarming curiosity, gently pushing back on Morganna's hunger for power and her distrust, suggesting that power comes to those who stop grasping for it and that being trusted feels good. The fragile rapport, built partly on their shared connection to Vexa, is briefly broken when a soaked stranger named Zarl stumbles in seeking refuge from the tide, and after Morganna's reflexive reach for her blaster, Fay coaxes her into letting the shivering newcomer sit by the fire.",
